    "long_instructions": "A scientist is analyzing data about meteorite landings. They want to determine if the number of meteorites is changing each year.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Landings.java</code>, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">countMatching()</code> method to return <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">1</code> if the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Meteorite</code> object landed in or after the given <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">year</code> AND the length of its class name is greater than <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">3</code>. Otherwise, return <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">0</code>.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">TheaterRunner.java</code>, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">countMatching()</code> method on all 5 <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Meteorite</code> objects, total the results, and pass that total into <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">drawResult()</code>.\r\n",
